1
00:00:00,066 --> 00:00:01,266
welcome back

2
00:00:01,266 --> 00:00:06,000
today we are going to complete the last challenge of GregTech New Horizons

3
00:00:06,066 --> 00:00:08,066
which is crafting a Stargate

4
00:00:08,433 --> 00:00:11,100
this things is going to require many items

5
00:00:11,100 --> 00:00:12,700
with many sub steps

6
00:00:12,700 --> 00:00:15,866
but it all boils down to three main parts

7
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:22,200
the main issue other than the expensive materials used is the time required to craft those

8
00:00:22,300 --> 00:00:24,833
to craft this stuff in a reasonable time

9
00:00:24,833 --> 00:00:27,233
we are going to do some overclocks

10
00:00:27,266 --> 00:00:30,366
but the real question is how much we should overclock

11
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:32,600
if we don't want to end up with a blackout

12
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:35,233
or waiting times longer by magnitudes

13
00:00:35,233 --> 00:00:37,833
we must find the optimal compromise

14
00:00:38,166 --> 00:00:39,566
to find the answer

15
00:00:39,566 --> 00:00:40,966
we first have to figure out

16
00:00:40,966 --> 00:00:43,200
how much energy we can produce

17
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:45,866
and while looking for a good generator

18
00:00:45,866 --> 00:00:50,200
our attention was caught by the shielded Legrandian annihilation matrix

19
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:52,466
a generator that runs on antimatter

20
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:53,600
of course

21
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:56,266
the question now is how do we make antimatter

22
00:00:56,266 --> 00:00:57,833
and how much we can make

23
00:00:57,966 --> 00:00:59,033
and it turns out

24
00:00:59,033 --> 00:01:02,966
it's made in one of those complex to manage multi blocks

25
00:01:03,033 --> 00:01:06,566
the semi stable Antimatter Stabilization Sequencer

26
00:01:06,766 --> 00:01:08,000
after quickly building it

27
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:11,033
and getting some antimatter to kick start the machine

28
00:01:11,033 --> 00:01:12,966
it is time to have some fun

29
00:01:13,266 --> 00:01:16,066
the first and most important thing we notice is that

30
00:01:16,066 --> 00:01:19,800
we must keep the antimatter evenly spread across the hatches

31
00:01:20,066 --> 00:01:22,233
and doing so is no joke

32
00:01:22,633 --> 00:01:23,233
anyways

33
00:01:23,233 --> 00:01:24,966
to do a little test

34
00:01:24,966 --> 00:01:28,833
we start by spreading our antimatter across all of the hatches

35
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:33,066
then after a bunch of tests

36
00:01:33,066 --> 00:01:38,633
we got to a point where we noticed how often we have to carefully find which hatch lost antimatter

37
00:01:38,900 --> 00:01:42,100
and after realizing that a simple cover won't be enough

38
00:01:42,100 --> 00:01:43,700
we did an SFM program

39
00:01:43,700 --> 00:01:47,033
that will keep a fixed amount of antimatter in each hatch

40
00:01:47,233 --> 00:01:47,766
with that

41
00:01:47,766 --> 00:01:50,433
we can now slowly build up some antimatter

42
00:01:50,433 --> 00:01:54,000
which we will then spread evenly across all the hatches once again

43
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:57,100
the more antimatter we keep in the machine

44
00:01:57,100 --> 00:01:58,700
the more we will produce

45
00:01:58,700 --> 00:02:01,600
but also the more energy will be used

46
00:02:01,700 --> 00:02:02,800
the question is now

47
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:05,633
how much antimatter we should keep in each hatch

48
00:02:05,633 --> 00:02:07,000
to find an answer

49
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:11,166
we can give a purpose to the calculus class we had to take in school

50
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:16,666
we shall plot the amount of energy in function of how much antimatter we place inside each hatch

51
00:02:16,666 --> 00:02:21,366
the blue line represents how much energy we can make with the produced antimatter

52
00:02:21,366 --> 00:02:25,200
while the red line will tell us how much energy that costed us

53
00:02:25,233 --> 00:02:27,633
we want to maximize the energy gain

54
00:02:27,633 --> 00:02:30,300
meaning the difference between the two lines

55
00:02:30,433 --> 00:02:33,233
which we can see here as a single function

56
00:02:33,233 --> 00:02:37,800
and the maximum we can get out of it is four Dyson spheres worth of energy

57
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:41,300
by keeping two and a half buckets of antimatter in each hatch

58
00:02:41,300 --> 00:02:41,800
however

59
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:45,100
by increasing the containment stabilization

60
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:47,433
the activation stabilization

61
00:02:47,466 --> 00:02:49,400
the gravity stabilization

62
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:51,700
and the magnetic stabilization

63
00:02:51,700 --> 00:02:55,666
we managed to make our energy gain graph go out of the screen

64
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:57,066
after some zooming

65
00:02:57,066 --> 00:03:01,800
we find out that our production can now reach 600 trillion EU/t

66
00:03:01,833 --> 00:03:04,800
by leaving 4 million antimatter in each hatch

67
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:07,466
and adding a bunch of other expensive stuff

68
00:03:07,466 --> 00:03:10,066
and that is one huge ball of antimatter

69
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:11,500
to turn it into energy

70
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:13,900
we are going to need one more machine

71
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:16,500
which isn't as complicated as the other one

72
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:20,833
one of the main requirements is to feed it with balanced amounts of materials

73
00:03:20,833 --> 00:03:25,766
which we can easily do with the same set up we used to feed the eyes of harmony

74
00:03:26,166 --> 00:03:28,900
this time the optimization problem is that

75
00:03:28,900 --> 00:03:32,166
we should insert as much fuel as possible in each batch

76
00:03:32,166 --> 00:03:35,100
but we are limited by the capacity of our lasers

77
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:38,833
with 16 UIV 1 million amps lasers

78
00:03:38,833 --> 00:03:42,233
we can produce as much as 100 Dyson Spheres

79
00:03:42,233 --> 00:03:45,300
but if we switch to UMV 4 million

80
00:03:45,300 --> 00:03:48,600
we can fill up an ultimate battery in 5 minutes

81
00:03:49,433 --> 00:03:51,466
that causes a bunch of issues

82
00:03:51,466 --> 00:03:53,566
but the best way to solve every problem

83
00:03:53,566 --> 00:03:55,266
is to use a better reactant

84
00:03:55,266 --> 00:03:57,233
and turn on wireless mode

85
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:58,966
the takeaway is that

86
00:03:58,966 --> 00:04:02,200
assuming we build a dozen of antimatter sequences

87
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:06,100
our whole energy production is going to be about 5 quadrillion EU/t

88
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:09,200
a number with 15 zeros

89
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:10,033
and from that

90
00:04:10,033 --> 00:04:12,300
we can get an idea of how much power

91
00:04:12,300 --> 00:04:14,233
we can throw at machines

92
00:04:14,300 --> 00:04:15,000
with that

93
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:20,100
we can now start working on all of the issues we will face while working on our star gate

94
00:04:20,300 --> 00:04:25,800
and the first problems started arising just when we were working on our new power production

95
00:04:26,033 --> 00:04:27,766
to have a high power output

96
00:04:27,766 --> 00:04:32,600
we had to insert various fluids in the antimatter sequencer to stabilize it

97
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:36,300
while some are either expensive stuff or byproducts

98
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:39,433
a curious one was the depleted naquadah fuel

99
00:04:39,433 --> 00:04:41,800
after upgrading our fuel production

100
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:45,566
we turned on full time our backup generators

101
00:04:45,566 --> 00:04:48,833
but it appears that those aren't burning fuel fast enough

102
00:04:48,866 --> 00:04:52,066
so we had to opt for a different way of wasting fuel

103
00:04:52,066 --> 00:04:54,000
energizing tesseracts

104
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:55,833
that is a slow process

105
00:04:55,833 --> 00:04:56,566
but luckily

106
00:04:56,566 --> 00:05:00,100
the oversized neutron activators we did for Naquadria

107
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:03,066
have the same kinetic energy working range

108
00:05:03,233 --> 00:05:06,300
after fixing the antimatter production materials

109
00:05:06,300 --> 00:05:09,400
we also realized that to react it efficiently

110
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:12,433
we are using liquid UMV superconductor

111
00:05:12,566 --> 00:05:13,866
the main issue here is that

112
00:05:13,866 --> 00:05:16,266
this stuff contains dragon blood

113
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:19,800
which we make with the draconic Evolution Fusion Crafter

114
00:05:19,866 --> 00:05:22,400
and that machine has a couple of issues

115
00:05:22,433 --> 00:05:25,800
the first one being that like many other machines

116
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:29,066
it won't accept multiamperage energy hatches

117
00:05:29,066 --> 00:05:34,400
which means that we won't be able to overclock it as much as we do with other machines

118
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:37,566
that usually means we just have to spam many of it

119
00:05:37,566 --> 00:05:39,366
but there is a second issue

120
00:05:39,433 --> 00:05:43,066
each Fusion Crafter requires a dense Gaia Spirit plate

121
00:05:43,066 --> 00:05:49,000
meaning we have to defeat more than two of the super annoying botania bosses for each machine of our array

122
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:49,666
however

123
00:05:49,666 --> 00:05:52,066
while working on that annoying task

124
00:05:52,066 --> 00:05:54,066
something gave us an idea

125
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:58,366
it appears that there is a mob with a high chance of dropping spawns

126
00:05:58,466 --> 00:06:00,800
with those we can craft dragon eggs

127
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:04,166
which can be turned into dragon blood with a normal mixer

128
00:06:04,300 --> 00:06:06,633
all we have to do is find the correct mob

129
00:06:06,633 --> 00:06:09,200
and start farming it in an industrial way

130
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:12,766
so that we can produce industrial amounts of spawns 

131
00:06:12,766 --> 00:06:13,166
eggs

132
00:06:13,166 --> 00:06:14,766
and dragon blood

133
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:17,566
now that we have fixed the energy production

134
00:06:17,566 --> 00:06:21,700
it is time to craft some energy hatches to put it to good use

135
00:06:21,700 --> 00:06:22,200
and here

136
00:06:22,200 --> 00:06:25,966
we realized that our universium production is too low

137
00:06:26,033 --> 00:06:27,200
to fix that

138
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:31,033
we are going to need a couple more of Astral Array fabricators

139
00:06:31,033 --> 00:06:34,766
and now the issue is the size of our crafting units

140
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:39,666
so I guess it's time for us to get a singularity crafting storage

141
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:42,433
and if we want a bunch of those

142
00:06:42,433 --> 00:06:46,366
we will need to go and take down a couple of Chaos Guardians 

143
00:06:46,366 --> 00:06:48,233
from each Guardian

144
00:06:48,233 --> 00:06:52,700
we get one of those crafting units with 8 exabytes of storage

145
00:06:53,100 --> 00:06:56,000
but now we lack of co processing units

146
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:58,166
instead we shall make better patterns

147
00:06:58,166 --> 00:07:00,966
with the new Pattern Optimization matrix

148
00:07:01,066 --> 00:07:06,433
that is because co-processors are needed to increase the amount of crafting steps done each second

149
00:07:06,433 --> 00:07:09,500
but instead of doing more steps at once

150
00:07:09,500 --> 00:07:11,600
we can make bigger steps

151
00:07:11,633 --> 00:07:12,500
to do so

152
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:16,400
we multiply the patterns with the help of the optimization matrix

153
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:20,666
which will make it so it won't take more steps than the amount we specify

154
00:07:20,766 --> 00:07:21,300
however

155
00:07:21,300 --> 00:07:24,666
doing so will also cause a lot of leftovers

156
00:07:24,666 --> 00:07:27,800
which are now filling up all of our storage cells

157
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:31,366
so we are going to upgrade to the artificial universe ones

158
00:07:31,366 --> 00:07:35,366
crafting one of those takes a fully charged Error tier battery

159
00:07:35,633 --> 00:07:37,100
to charge such battery

160
00:07:37,100 --> 00:07:38,900
we shall use an energy infuser

161
00:07:38,900 --> 00:07:44,066
powered by the forbidden energy hatch that carries the power of a dozen of antimatter generators

162
00:07:44,066 --> 00:07:46,066
and even with such power

163
00:07:46,066 --> 00:07:49,300
it will still take a few minutes to charge up our battery

164
00:07:49,300 --> 00:07:50,100
meanwhile

165
00:07:50,100 --> 00:07:53,966
we managed to complete our first item with Star Gate in its name

166
00:07:53,966 --> 00:07:56,866
this was a small step in our progression

167
00:07:56,866 --> 00:07:59,433
but a huge leap in resource usage

168
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:03,800
so we added more astral array fabricators to our eye of harmony

169
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:06,100
thus making a lot of universium

170
00:08:06,366 --> 00:08:09,566
and that is using half of our current power production

171
00:08:09,566 --> 00:08:10,966
which in turn

172
00:08:10,966 --> 00:08:14,500
is also using a quarter of our universium production

173
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:15,000
but

174
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:18,700
we have enough left over to slowly start building our star gate

175
00:08:19,266 --> 00:08:22,466
and now we will be looking for all of the bottlenecks

176
00:08:22,566 --> 00:08:25,366
such as that old HV fluid solidifier

177
00:08:25,833 --> 00:08:30,166
or some crafting table recipes that are being done one at a time

178
00:08:30,633 --> 00:08:33,666
luckily most of those have an assembler alternative

179
00:08:34,066 --> 00:08:37,200
which of course we will parallelize

180
00:08:37,566 --> 00:08:41,200
then we have machines that are still using small input buses

181
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:45,066
we shall move the used patterns to a proper crafting bus

182
00:08:45,066 --> 00:08:48,100
also there are some invalid patterns laying around

183
00:08:48,100 --> 00:08:51,400
due to stuff that didn't pass the beta tests

184
00:08:51,666 --> 00:08:56,300
and we must not forget about doing some maintenance to our older setups

185
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:59,433
I mean we must not forget to upgrade everything

186
00:08:59,433 --> 00:09:01,966
with the best technology at our disposal

187
00:09:02,100 --> 00:09:04,800
finally we shall start adding more machines

188
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:08,700
where adding more power would start to make the consumption relevant

189
00:09:09,066 --> 00:09:12,666
like our generic purpose parallel assembly line setup

190
00:09:12,666 --> 00:09:15,466
which now will become multi machine parallel

191
00:09:15,566 --> 00:09:17,200
and all of those assembly lines

192
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:19,166
reminded us of our circuit factory

193
00:09:19,166 --> 00:09:22,433
which seems to start to struggle with the new demands

194
00:09:22,566 --> 00:09:25,166
since it wasn't easy to expand that one

195
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,766
we made new factories

196
00:09:26,833 --> 00:09:28,700
one for each circuit tier

197
00:09:28,866 --> 00:09:31,400
and that was a lot of assembly lines

198
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:34,700
with a lot of expensive UXV energy hatches

199
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:38,466
and of course those are only assembling circuits

200
00:09:38,466 --> 00:09:41,766
we needed a lot of other machines to keep up with all of the

201
00:09:41,766 --> 00:09:47,033
circuit boards, memory, SMDs, cables, screws, weird materials

202
00:09:47,033 --> 00:09:49,566
and everything else that goes into the circuits

203
00:09:49,766 --> 00:09:54,300
and all of those machines are just the starting point of our Star Gate factory

204
00:09:54,466 --> 00:09:58,666
which for now is a factory of UXV energy hatches

205
00:09:58,800 --> 00:09:59,333
however

206
00:09:59,333 --> 00:10:03,466
overclocking and building more machines isn't always the solution

207
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:06,100
our black hole had a special Redstone control

208
00:10:06,100 --> 00:10:09,300
to optimize its crafting to last 3 minutes

209
00:10:09,466 --> 00:10:15,566
the idea was to try to use the bonus parallel from the decaying black hole as much as possible

210
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:16,433
however

211
00:10:16,433 --> 00:10:19,600
one of the Stargate parts requires an element that

212
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:21,100
even with overclocks

213
00:10:21,100 --> 00:10:23,733
can't be made in less than a quarter of hour

214
00:10:23,733 --> 00:10:27,766
since we don't want to have to wait that much for each recipe change

215
00:10:27,766 --> 00:10:29,633
we had to make a second black hole

216
00:10:29,633 --> 00:10:32,033
with special settings for that recipe

217
00:10:32,166 --> 00:10:37,900
but the real issue here is the amount of space time required to keep a black hole open for that much time

218
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,466
since it doubles every 30 seconds

219
00:10:40,466 --> 00:10:44,766
we are going to need almost 1 billion per second in the last phase

220
00:10:44,766 --> 00:10:48,500
exactly half of the maximum we can input each update

221
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:52,466
which is also more than what an export bus can transfer

222
00:10:52,666 --> 00:10:55,500
next since we were managing black holes

223
00:10:55,500 --> 00:10:57,266
we also made a third one

224
00:10:57,466 --> 00:11:01,966
this one will make eternal singularities passively with a timer circuit

225
00:11:02,566 --> 00:11:03,300
finally

226
00:11:03,300 --> 00:11:06,666
there is one last ingredient which we can't make yet

227
00:11:06,666 --> 00:11:08,266
the Star Gate crystal

228
00:11:08,366 --> 00:11:11,300
that one requires a special ingredient

229
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:12,466
graviton shards

230
00:11:12,666 --> 00:11:15,000
the same we use for upgrading our gorge

231
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:16,433
and which we have none of

232
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:18,666
we have a button for retrieving those

233
00:11:18,666 --> 00:11:20,666
but we first need to gather some

234
00:11:20,833 --> 00:11:21,500
to do so

235
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:24,233
we have to reach more milestones

236
00:11:24,433 --> 00:11:27,700
and the easiest one to do now is the composition one

237
00:11:27,866 --> 00:11:31,766
this one requires us to add new modules or structure rings

238
00:11:31,766 --> 00:11:35,366
so time to get an even cooler looking forge

239
00:11:35,466 --> 00:11:37,066
and I know it looks majestic

240
00:11:37,066 --> 00:11:39,266
and that we could stare at it for hours

241
00:11:39,266 --> 00:11:40,300
but we have to move on

242
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:43,900
since we now have unlocked a bunch of Graviton Shards

243
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:47,500
actually there's more milestones we need to do

244
00:11:47,766 --> 00:11:50,900
we can easily buy one with some universium

245
00:11:51,166 --> 00:11:55,166
the fuel consumption was exponential with the transcendent residue

246
00:11:55,166 --> 00:11:57,666
but it's not with constrained star matter

247
00:11:57,666 --> 00:11:59,633
so we can just dump enough at once

248
00:11:59,633 --> 00:12:01,633
to complete the fuel milestone

249
00:12:01,666 --> 00:12:04,500
and that was probably not a good usage of fuel

250
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:07,666
however by unlocking all of the milestones

251
00:12:07,666 --> 00:12:10,766
some new instructions appeared in our forge

252
00:12:10,766 --> 00:12:13,033
and we now have enough graviton shards

253
00:12:13,033 --> 00:12:16,800
to proceed with the mixing for the base dust required by the crystal

254
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:20,766
and after also doing some more stuff in our cyclotrons

255
00:12:20,766 --> 00:12:22,666
we managed to get the dust

256
00:12:22,833 --> 00:12:25,566
then we prepare some Stargate crystal slurry

257
00:12:25,566 --> 00:12:28,000
and drop everything in a blast furnace

258
00:12:28,333 --> 00:12:28,833
however

259
00:12:28,833 --> 00:12:31,833
it looks like this recipe needs more heat

260
00:12:32,100 --> 00:12:35,466
so we crank on the thermostat to the required temperature

261
00:12:35,633 --> 00:12:37,966
and that is giving us a lot of boosts

262
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:38,933
finally

263
00:12:38,933 --> 00:12:43,433
we also had to increase the processing power to start our crafting

264
00:12:43,766 --> 00:12:46,033
and while the crystals were cooking

265
00:12:46,033 --> 00:12:49,433
we noticed that our magmatter production wasn't working

266
00:12:49,766 --> 00:12:51,233
upon a quick inspection

267
00:12:51,233 --> 00:12:53,566
it looked like everything was in place

268
00:12:53,700 --> 00:12:57,366
so let's get reminded of how that machine works

269
00:12:57,533 --> 00:12:58,833
when we turn it on

270
00:12:58,833 --> 00:13:01,500
we will get 2 fluids and a tiny dust

271
00:13:01,666 --> 00:13:02,833
to get magmatter

272
00:13:02,833 --> 00:13:08,400
we have to input back the two fluids and plasma of the material the tiny dust is made out of

273
00:13:08,466 --> 00:13:09,666
that used to work fine

274
00:13:09,666 --> 00:13:14,833
and allowed us to just shove everything the machine could possibly want to get the magmatter

275
00:13:15,133 --> 00:13:17,233
however that feature has been patched

276
00:13:17,233 --> 00:13:18,700
because it actually was a bug

277
00:13:18,700 --> 00:13:26,666
and we now must input an amount of plasma that is exactly 144 times the difference between the other two fluids

278
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:30,033
and now we must find a way of automating that

279
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:35,433
we start by getting each one of the three starting outputs in a dedicated storage

280
00:13:35,633 --> 00:13:38,466
then using the good old custom pattern trick

281
00:13:38,466 --> 00:13:40,400
and the laggy crafting cards

282
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:43,200
we get out of there the two fluids in equal amounts

283
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:45,166
until only one is left

284
00:13:45,300 --> 00:13:46,266
at that point

285
00:13:46,266 --> 00:13:48,433
the fluid is moved to another tank

286
00:13:48,433 --> 00:13:52,766
where a different subnetwork will trade each milliliter bucket for a cell

287
00:13:52,766 --> 00:13:58,066
we send those cells to take the correct fluid selected by a Redstone contraption

288
00:13:58,266 --> 00:14:01,233
thus having the correct amount of fluid for our magmatter

289
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:02,566
or so we thought

290
00:14:02,566 --> 00:14:05,966
until we found out that cells carry a whole bucket

291
00:14:06,166 --> 00:14:10,300
so we switched to the more precise volumetric flasks

292
00:14:10,666 --> 00:14:13,033
that solved the mag matter issues

293
00:14:13,033 --> 00:14:17,200
but we also have to find a solution for the quark gluon plasma fluid

294
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:20,166
which has some more possible materials in it

295
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:24,466
this time instead of overengineered Redstone setups

296
00:14:24,466 --> 00:14:26,833
we shall use an even worse approach

297
00:14:26,833 --> 00:14:29,666
we brute force the task using SFM

298
00:14:29,833 --> 00:14:32,866
and since we couldn't find a solution on Stack Overflow

299
00:14:32,866 --> 00:14:34,766
and we are afraid of for loops

300
00:14:34,766 --> 00:14:36,566
we shall do a long chain of elseif

301
00:14:36,566 --> 00:14:38,700
as in the programmer humor memes

302
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:41,233
but hey it works

303
00:14:41,466 --> 00:14:43,100
anyways with that

304
00:14:43,100 --> 00:14:46,566
we are now ready to start working on the craft of our star gate

305
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:48,266
that thing has many steps

306
00:14:48,266 --> 00:14:50,200
and requires trillions of items

307
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:53,800
so we are going to split the task in more smaller ones

308
00:14:54,066 --> 00:14:57,333
and while the small tasks are being done autonomously by AE2

309
00:14:57,333 --> 00:15:00,900
we can work on improving our infrastructure

310
00:15:01,366 --> 00:15:04,566
the first thing we shall fix is our power production

311
00:15:04,766 --> 00:15:08,300
and of course that will need a lot of universium

312
00:15:08,300 --> 00:15:11,800
which we can make with some astral arrays in a eye of harmony

313
00:15:12,266 --> 00:15:14,300
then we build thousands of machines

314
00:15:14,300 --> 00:15:16,466
to speed up the crafting of everything

315
00:15:16,900 --> 00:15:17,366
finally

316
00:15:17,366 --> 00:15:21,700
we overclock the slow stuff as much as our power production allows

317
00:15:21,700 --> 00:15:26,766
cutting down the crafting time of the slowest parts by a factor of 1000

318
00:15:27,066 --> 00:15:29,566
and now we have reached the TPS cap

319
00:15:29,566 --> 00:15:33,200
so we just sit and watch our star gate being crafted

320
00:15:33,266 --> 00:15:34,900
this took a lot of time

321
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:37,066
but we managed to slowly build it

322
00:15:37,100 --> 00:15:39,633
and here we have our latest creation

323
00:15:39,700 --> 00:15:40,266
however

324
00:15:40,266 --> 00:15:43,100
while we completed the last quest of the mod pack

325
00:15:43,100 --> 00:15:44,900
we aren't fully done yet

326
00:15:44,966 --> 00:15:45,466
indeed

327
00:15:45,466 --> 00:15:48,833
this device is useless if we don't have a second one

328
00:15:48,866 --> 00:15:50,766
so we AFK a little bit more

329
00:15:50,766 --> 00:15:53,400
while ae2 builds us a second one

330
00:15:53,500 --> 00:15:55,766
after building it in some hidden place

331
00:15:55,766 --> 00:15:59,700
we can connect to it by dialing its address in our main star gate

332
00:15:59,700 --> 00:16:02,866
we confirm it and then we stare at the animation

333
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:13,666
and now it's time to show the mystical place this portal will bring us to

334
00:16:13,900 --> 00:16:15,033
as you can see

335
00:16:15,033 --> 00:16:19,566
this place has some weird green stuff spread across all over the place

336
00:16:19,633 --> 00:16:21,766
but I think we did enough for today

337
00:16:21,766 --> 00:16:25,766
we can try to think about touching this stuff in the next season

338
00:16:25,866 --> 00:16:27,066
and as usual

339
00:16:27,066 --> 00:16:28,700
before greetings

340
00:16:28,700 --> 00:16:32,200
we shall reflect on what we Learned in today's episode

341
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:36,433
after all the drops of sweat and tears we did to make it this far

342
00:16:36,433 --> 00:16:40,000
the real prize is not the reward we get from the quest completion

343
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:43,100
but the piles of stone dust we made along the way

344
00:16:43,100 --> 00:16:44,000
bye bye

345
00:00:00,066 --> 00:00:01,266
欢迎回来

346
00:00:01,266 --> 00:00:06,000
今天我们要完成GTNH最后一个挑战

347
00:00:06,066 --> 00:00:08,066
制作星门

348
00:00:08,433 --> 00:00:11,100
它需要很多材料

349
00:00:11,100 --> 00:00:12,700
有许多子步骤

350
00:00:12,700 --> 00:00:15,866
但这一切都归结为三个主要部分

351
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:18,333

主要问题除了要使用昂贵材料


352
00:00:18,333 --> 00:00:22,233

还有就是它们制作它们消耗的巨额时间


353
00:00:22,300 --> 00:00:24,833
在合理的时间内制作这些东西

354
00:00:24,833 --> 00:00:27,233
我们要做一些超频

355
00:00:27,266 --> 00:00:30,366
而真正的问题是超频方案

356
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:32,600
如果不想跳电

357
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:35,233
或者几何级增长等待时间

358
00:00:35,233 --> 00:00:37,833
我们必须找到最佳的折衷方案

359
00:00:38,166 --> 00:00:39,566
要找到答案

360
00:00:39,566 --> 00:00:40,966
我们首先要弄清楚

361
00:00:40,966 --> 00:00:43,200
我们能产生多少能量

362
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:45,866
在寻找好的发电机的同时

363
00:00:45,866 --> 00:00:50,200
我们的注意力被屏蔽拉格朗日湮灭矩阵吸引住了

364
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:52,466
一个依靠反物质发电的机器

365
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:53,600
当然

366
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:56,266
现在的问题是我们如何制造反物质

367
00:00:56,266 --> 00:00:57,833
以及能做多少

368
00:00:57,966 --> 00:00:59,033
结果证明

369
00:00:59,033 --> 00:01:02,966
它是在一个需要复杂管理的多方块中产生的

370
00:01:03,033 --> 00:01:06,566
半稳定反物质稳定定序器

371
00:01:06,766 --> 00:01:08,000
快速建造它后

372
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:11,033
并获得一些反物质来启动机器

373
00:01:11,033 --> 00:01:12,966
是时候找点乐子了

374
00:01:13,266 --> 00:01:16,066
我们注意到的第一件也是最重要的事情是

375
00:01:16,066 --> 00:01:19,800
我们必须让反物质均匀分布在各个仓室

376
00:01:20,066 --> 00:01:22,233
而且这可不是儿戏

377
00:01:22,633 --> 00:01:23,233
不管怎样

378
00:01:23,233 --> 00:01:24,966
做一个小测试

379
00:01:24,966 --> 00:01:28,833
我们首先把反物质分散到所有舱室

380
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:33,066
然后经过一系列测试

381
00:01:33,066 --> 00:01:38,633
我们已经注意到必须时常提防是否有仓室缺少了反物质

382
00:01:38,900 --> 00:01:42,100
在意识到一个简单的覆盖板是不够的之后

383
00:01:42,100 --> 00:01:43,700
我们做了一个SFM程序

384
00:01:43,700 --> 00:01:47,033
保证每个舱口都有固定数量的反物质

385
00:01:47,233 --> 00:01:47,766
有了那个

386
00:01:47,766 --> 00:01:50,433
我们现在可以慢慢制造一些反物质

387
00:01:50,433 --> 00:01:54,000
然后我们将再次均匀地分布在所有舱口

388
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:57,100
我们留在机器里的反物质越多

389
00:01:57,100 --> 00:01:58,700
我们生产的就越多

390
00:01:58,700 --> 00:02:01,600
但也会使用更多的能量

391
00:02:01,700 --> 00:02:02,800
现在的问题是

392
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:05,633
每个仓室应该放多少反物质

393
00:02:05,633 --> 00:02:07,000

要得出答案


394
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:11,166

学校里上的微积分课就有了存在价值


395
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:16,666
根据每个仓室内的反物质数量来绘制能量函数

396
00:02:16,666 --> 00:02:21,366
蓝线代表产生的反物质能产生多少能量

397
00:02:21,366 --> 00:02:25,200
而红线会告诉我们消耗了多少能量

398
00:02:25,233 --> 00:02:27,633
我们想最大化发电量

399
00:02:27,633 --> 00:02:30,300
也就是两条线的差值

400
00:02:30,433 --> 00:02:33,233
我们可以把它看成单一函数

401
00:02:33,233 --> 00:02:37,800
在每个仓室里放两桶半反物质

402
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:41,300
我们能得到四个戴森球能量的最大发电量

403
00:02:41,300 --> 00:02:41,800
然而

404
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:45,100
通过提高遏制稳定性

405
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:47,433
激活稳定化

406
00:02:47,466 --> 00:02:49,400
重力稳定

407
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:51,700
磁稳定

408
00:02:51,700 --> 00:02:55,666
我们设法让发电图超出屏幕

409
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:57,066
放大后

410
00:02:57,066 --> 00:03:01,800
我们发现发电量现在可以达到600万亿 EU/t

411
00:03:01,833 --> 00:03:04,800
此时每个仓室有4ML反物质

412
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:07,466
并需要添加一堆其他昂贵的东西

413
00:03:07,466 --> 00:03:10,066
那是一个巨大的反物质球

414
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:11,500
将其转化为能量

415
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:13,900
我们还需要一台机器

416
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:16,500
这个比较简单

417
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:20,833
其中一个主要要求是给予其可平衡的材料

418
00:03:20,833 --> 00:03:25,766

使用我们在鸿蒙之眼上用过的相同装置可以轻松解决


419
00:03:26,166 --> 00:03:28,900
现在要优化的问题是

420
00:03:28,900 --> 00:03:32,166
应该在每批中输入尽可能多的燃料

421
00:03:32,166 --> 00:03:35,100
但限制在于激光仓的容量

422
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:38,833
使用16个UIV 100万A的激光源仓

423
00:03:38,833 --> 00:03:42,233
发电量可以与100个戴森球相当

424
00:03:42,233 --> 00:03:45,300
但是如果我们换成UMV 400万A

425
00:03:45,300 --> 00:03:48,600
我们可以在5分钟内充满终极电池

426
00:03:49,433 --> 00:03:51,466
这会导致很多问题

427
00:03:51,466 --> 00:03:53,566
但解决每个问题的最好方法

428
00:03:53,566 --> 00:03:55,266
就是使用更好的反应物

429
00:03:55,266 --> 00:03:57,233
并打开无线模式

430
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:58,966
所以结论是

431
00:03:58,966 --> 00:04:02,200
假设我们建立了一堆反物质序列

432
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:06,100
发电量将达到5千万亿 EU/t

433
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:09,200
一个有15个零的数字

434
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:10,033
从这个数字里

435
00:04:10,033 --> 00:04:12,300
我们可以知道

436
00:04:12,300 --> 00:04:14,233
可以将多少电输入进机器

437
00:04:14,300 --> 00:04:15,000
有了那个

438
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:20,100
我们现在可以开始解决所有会在星门制作中出现的问题

439
00:04:20,300 --> 00:04:23,466
就在着手于新能源生产时

440
00:04:23,466 --> 00:04:25,800
第一个问题出现了

441
00:04:26,033 --> 00:04:27,766
要想有高功率输出

442
00:04:27,766 --> 00:04:32,600
我们必须在反物质定序器中输入各种液体来稳定它

443
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:36,300
而有些要么是昂贵的东西，要么是副产品

444
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:39,433

其中一种奇怪的流体是耗尽的硅岩燃料


445
00:04:39,433 --> 00:04:41,800
在我们的燃料生产升级后

446
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:45,566

我们把备用发电机一直开着


447
00:04:45,566 --> 00:04:48,833
但看起来这些燃料燃烧得不够快

448
00:04:48,866 --> 00:04:52,066
所以我们不得不选择另一种方式来浪费燃料

449
00:04:52,066 --> 00:04:54,000
中子活化超立方体

450
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:55,833
这是一个缓慢的过程

451
00:04:55,833 --> 00:04:56,566
但幸运的是

452
00:04:56,566 --> 00:05:00,100
我们为硅岩所准备的中子活化器

453
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:03,066
具有相同的动能工作范围

454
00:05:03,233 --> 00:05:06,300

解决反物质生产材料后


455
00:05:06,300 --> 00:05:09,400
我们也意识到，为了有效地反应

456
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:12,433

我们要消耗液态UMV超导粗胚


457
00:05:12,566 --> 00:05:13,866
这里的主要问题是

458
00:05:13,866 --> 00:05:16,266
这东西含有龙血

459
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:19,800
我们正在使用龙研聚合装置制作

460
00:05:19,866 --> 00:05:22,400
那台机器有几个问题

461
00:05:22,433 --> 00:05:25,800
第一个是像许多其他机器一样

462
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:29,066
它不接受多安能源仓

463
00:05:29,066 --> 00:05:34,400
这意味着我们不能像用其他机器那样超频

464
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:37,566
这通常意味着我们只需要堆量

465
00:05:37,566 --> 00:05:39,366
但还有第二个问题

466
00:05:39,433 --> 00:05:43,066
每个机器都需要致密盖亚之魂大板

467
00:05:43,066 --> 00:05:49,000
这意味着我们必须为阵列中的每台机器击败两个以上的惹人厌的植物魔法的boss

468
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:49,666
然而

469
00:05:49,666 --> 00:05:52,066
在做那个烦人的任务时

470
00:05:52,066 --> 00:05:54,066
某种东西让我们灵光一现

471
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:58,366
似乎有个怪有很高的几率掉率刷怪蛋

472
00:05:58,466 --> 00:06:00,800
用这些我们可以制作龙蛋

473
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:04,166
通过普通的搅拌可以变成龙血

474
00:06:04,300 --> 00:06:06,633
我们要做的就是找到正确的怪物

475
00:06:06,633 --> 00:06:09,200
并进行工业化生产

476
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:12,766
这样我们就可以生产大量的刷怪蛋

477
00:06:12,766 --> 00:06:13,766
龙蛋

478
00:06:13,766 --> 00:06:14,766
还有龙血

479
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:17,566
现在我们已经修好了发电

480
00:06:17,566 --> 00:06:21,700
是时候制作一些能源仓来充分利用它了

481
00:06:21,700 --> 00:06:22,200
这里

482
00:06:22,200 --> 00:06:25,966
我们意识到宇宙素的产量太低了

483
00:06:26,033 --> 00:06:27,200
解决这个问题

484
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:31,033
我们需要再做几个星阵

485
00:06:31,033 --> 00:06:34,766
现在的问题是CPU的大小

486
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:39,666
所以我想是时候做一个奇点合成存储单元了

487
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:42,433

如果我们想多做一些


488
00:06:42,433 --> 00:06:46,366
我们得去干掉些混沌守卫 

489
00:06:46,366 --> 00:06:48,233
每干掉一个

490
00:06:48,233 --> 00:06:52,700
便可以得到一个有8EB存储空间的合成单元

491
00:06:53,100 --> 00:06:56,000
现在缺少的是并行单元

492
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:58,166
相反，我们将开始优化样板

493
00:06:58,166 --> 00:07:00,966
使用新的样板优化矩阵

494
00:07:01,066 --> 00:07:06,433
这是因为并行能增加每秒完成的制作步骤的数量

495
00:07:06,433 --> 00:07:09,500
不过与其多走几步

496
00:07:09,500 --> 00:07:11,600
不如跨大脚步

497
00:07:11,633 --> 00:07:12,500
为此

498
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:16,400
我们借助优化矩阵将模板相乘

499
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:20,666
这将使最大步骤控制在我们设定的数量内

500
00:07:20,766 --> 00:07:21,300
然而

501
00:07:21,300 --> 00:07:24,666
这样做也会造成很多冗余

502
00:07:24,666 --> 00:07:27,800
我们的存储元件已经被填满了

503
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:31,366
所以我们要升级到人造宇宙版

504
00:07:31,366 --> 00:07:35,366
制造其中一个需要充满电的error等级电池

505
00:07:35,633 --> 00:07:37,100
要给它充电

506
00:07:37,100 --> 00:07:38,900
我们将使用能量注入器

507
00:07:38,900 --> 00:07:44,066
由携带十几个反物质发生器的能量的禁忌能量仓供电

508
00:07:44,066 --> 00:07:46,066
即使有这样的电力

509
00:07:46,066 --> 00:07:49,300
给电池充电仍然需要几分钟

510
00:07:49,300 --> 00:07:50,100
同时

511
00:07:50,100 --> 00:07:53,966
我们已经完成了第一个带有星门名字的物品了

512
00:07:53,966 --> 00:07:56,866
这只是我们进步的一小步

513
00:07:56,866 --> 00:07:59,433
但是是资源使用的巨大飞跃

514
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:03,800
所以我们在鸿蒙之眼中添加了更多星阵

515
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:06,100
这会产出大量宇宙素

516
00:08:06,366 --> 00:08:09,566
而这也使用了目前一半的电力生产

517
00:08:09,566 --> 00:08:10,966
反过来

518
00:08:10,966 --> 00:08:14,500
它也使用了四分之一的宇宙素

519
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:15,000
但是

520
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:18,700
用于制作星门的量还是绰绰有余

521
00:08:19,266 --> 00:08:22,466
现在我们将寻找所有的瓶颈

522
00:08:22,566 --> 00:08:25,366
比如那个旧的HV流体固化器

523
00:08:25,833 --> 00:08:30,166
或者一些一次只做一个的样板

524
00:08:30,633 --> 00:08:33,666
幸运的是，其中大多数都有组装机配方

525
00:08:34,066 --> 00:08:37,200

我们当然会让它们能够并行生产


526
00:08:37,566 --> 00:08:41,200
然后我们有机器仍然使用小型输入总线

527
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:45,066
我们把使用过的样板转移到正确的总成中

528
00:08:45,066 --> 00:08:48,100
而这也有些无效样板

529
00:08:48,100 --> 00:08:51,400
因为其没活过测试版

530
00:08:51,666 --> 00:08:56,300
我们不能忘记对旧设备进行一些维护

531
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:59,433
意思是应该全部进行升级

532
00:08:59,433 --> 00:09:01,966
用我们掌握的最好的技术

533
00:09:02,100 --> 00:09:04,800
最后我们将开始添加更多机器

534
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:08,700

直到加更多能源会造成不容小看的电量消耗


535
00:09:09,066 --> 00:09:12,666
就像我们的通用并行装配线设置一样

536
00:09:12,666 --> 00:09:15,466
现在将成为多机并行

537
00:09:15,566 --> 00:09:17,200
所有这些装配线

538
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:19,166
让我们想起了电路工厂

539
00:09:19,166 --> 00:09:22,433
它似乎跟不上新的需求了

540
00:09:22,566 --> 00:09:25,166
扩展这个可不简单

541
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,766
我们建造了新工厂

542
00:09:26,833 --> 00:09:28,700
每个电路一个

543
00:09:28,866 --> 00:09:31,400
这可是很多装配线

544
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:34,700
有很多昂贵的UXV能源仓

545
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:38,466
当然，这些只用来组装电路

546
00:09:38,466 --> 00:09:41,766
我们需要很多其他机器来跟上所有的

547
00:09:41,766 --> 00:09:47,033
电路板、内存、SMD、电缆、螺丝、奇怪的材料

548
00:09:47,033 --> 00:09:49,566
以及其他装配电路的东西

549
00:09:49,766 --> 00:09:54,300
所有这些机器只是我们星门工厂的起点

550
00:09:54,466 --> 00:09:58,666
而工厂已全面装设UXV能源仓

551
00:09:58,800 --> 00:09:59,333
然而

552
00:09:59,333 --> 00:10:03,466
超频和制造更多机器并不总是解决方案

553
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:06,100
我们的黑洞有一个特殊的红石控制装置

554
00:10:06,100 --> 00:10:09,300
将其合成优化到持续3分钟

555
00:10:09,466 --> 00:10:15,566
宗旨是尽可能多地利用衰变黑洞奖励的并行

556
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:16,433
然而

557
00:10:16,433 --> 00:10:19,600
星门部件的一部分

558
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:21,100
即使有超频

559
00:10:21,100 --> 00:10:23,733
至少需要15分钟制作

560
00:10:23,733 --> 00:10:27,766
因为我们不想每次更换配方都要等那么久

561
00:10:27,766 --> 00:10:29,633
我们必须制造第二个黑洞

562
00:10:29,633 --> 00:10:32,033
此配方有个特殊设置

563
00:10:32,166 --> 00:10:37,900
但真正的问题是要保持此黑洞开启所需要的大量时空

564
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,466
因为它每30秒翻倍一次

565
00:10:40,466 --> 00:10:44,766
在最后阶段我们需要每秒10亿

566
00:10:44,766 --> 00:10:48,500
正好是我们每次更新可以输入的最大值的一半

567
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:52,466
这也比输出仓能转移的多

568
00:10:52,666 --> 00:10:55,500
接下来，既然我们在做黑洞的东西

569
00:10:55,500 --> 00:10:57,266
我们还做了第三个

570
00:10:57,466 --> 00:11:01,966
这个会用计时器电路被动制造永恒奇点

571
00:11:02,566 --> 00:11:03,300
最后

572
00:11:03,300 --> 00:11:06,666
还有最后一种成分我们做不出来

573
00:11:06,666 --> 00:11:08,266
星门水晶

574
00:11:08,366 --> 00:11:11,300
它需要特殊材料

575
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:12,466
引力子碎片

576
00:11:12,666 --> 00:11:15,000
和我们用来升级神锻的一样

577
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:16,433
而我们一个都没有

578
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:18,666
我们有一个用于提取引力子碎片的按钮

579
00:11:18,666 --> 00:11:20,666
但我们首先需要收集一些

580
00:11:20,833 --> 00:11:21,500
为此

581
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:24,233
我们必须达到更多的里程碑

582
00:11:24,433 --> 00:11:27,700
现在最简单的是结构

583
00:11:27,866 --> 00:11:31,766
这个需要我们添加新的模块或环

584
00:11:31,766 --> 00:11:35,366
所以是时候换一个更酷的外观了

585
00:11:35,466 --> 00:11:37,066
我知道它看起来很壮观

586
00:11:37,066 --> 00:11:39,266
我们可以看它旋转几小时

587
00:11:39,266 --> 00:11:40,300
但我们必须继续前进

588
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:43,900
因为我们已经解锁了一堆引力子碎片

589
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:47,500
事实上，我们需要做更多的里程碑

590
00:11:47,766 --> 00:11:50,900
我们可以很容易地用一些宇宙素买到一个

591
00:11:51,166 --> 00:11:55,166
燃料消耗与超维度残留成指数关系

592
00:11:55,166 --> 00:11:57,666
但对于蓝框岩浆可不是

593
00:11:57,666 --> 00:11:59,633
所以我们可以一次输入足够多的燃料

594
00:11:59,633 --> 00:12:01,633
完成燃料里程碑

595
00:12:01,666 --> 00:12:04,500
这可能不是一个正确的燃料用途

596
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:07,666
但是通过解锁所有里程碑

597
00:12:07,666 --> 00:12:10,766
我们的神锻里出现了一些新的指示

598
00:12:10,766 --> 00:12:13,033
我们现在有足够的引力子碎片

599
00:12:13,033 --> 00:12:16,800
用于混合出星门水晶所需的基础粉尘

600
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:20,766
在回旋加速器中做了更多的事情之后

601
00:12:20,766 --> 00:12:22,666
我们弄到了所需的粉

602
00:12:22,833 --> 00:12:25,566
然后我们准备一些星门水晶浆液

603
00:12:25,566 --> 00:12:28,000
并把所有东西扔进高炉

604
00:12:28,333 --> 00:12:28,833
然而

605
00:12:28,833 --> 00:12:31,833
看起来这个配方需要更高的炉温

606
00:12:32,100 --> 00:12:35,466
所以我们把炉温调制要求值

607
00:12:35,633 --> 00:12:37,966
这给了我们很大的提升

608
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:38,933
最后

609
00:12:38,933 --> 00:12:43,433
我们还必须增加处理电压来开始制作

610
00:12:43,766 --> 00:12:46,033
当水晶在烹饪的时候

611
00:12:46,033 --> 00:12:49,433
我们注意到磁物质未能正常生产

612
00:12:49,766 --> 00:12:51,233
经过快速检查

613
00:12:51,233 --> 00:12:53,566
看起来一切都就位了

614
00:12:53,700 --> 00:12:57,366
让我们来看看这台机器是如何工作的

615
00:12:57,533 --> 00:12:58,833
当我们打开它时

616
00:12:58,833 --> 00:13:01,500
我们会得到2种液体和一种小撮粉

617
00:13:01,666 --> 00:13:02,833
得到磁物质

618
00:13:02,833 --> 00:13:08,400
我们必须输入两种液体和小撮粉对应的等离子体

619
00:13:08,466 --> 00:13:09,666
之前一切正常

620
00:13:09,666 --> 00:13:14,833
允许我们供给机器可能想要的所有材料

621
00:13:15,133 --> 00:13:17,233

但是这个特性已经被修复了


622
00:13:17,233 --> 00:13:18,700
因为那其实是bug

623
00:13:18,700 --> 00:13:26,666
我们现在必须输入的等离子量正好是另外两种液体差的144倍

624
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:30,033
现在我们必须找到一种自动化的方法

625
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:35,433
我们首先将三个起始输出中的每一个都放入专用存储中

626
00:13:35,633 --> 00:13:38,466
然后使用古老的自定义模板技巧

627
00:13:38,466 --> 00:13:40,400
还有略卡顿的合成卡

628
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:43,200
我们从那里取出等量的两种液体

629
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:45,166

直到只剩下一种


630
00:13:45,300 --> 00:13:46,266
到那时

631
00:13:46,266 --> 00:13:48,433
液体被转移到另一个罐中

632
00:13:48,433 --> 00:13:52,766
其中，不同的子网络将把每个毫升交换出一个空单元

633
00:13:52,766 --> 00:13:58,066
我们把单元通过红石装置来获取正确的液体输入

634
00:13:58,266 --> 00:14:01,233
从而为我们的磁物质提供正确数量的液体

635
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:02,566
或许我们是这么想的

636
00:14:02,566 --> 00:14:05,966

直到我们发现空单元一次必须装一桶


637
00:14:06,166 --> 00:14:10,300
所以我们改用更精确的容积瓶

638
00:14:10,666 --> 00:14:13,033
这解决了磁物质问题

639
00:14:13,033 --> 00:14:17,200
但是我们也必须完成夸克胶子等离子体的自动化

640
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:20,166

生产它有更多可以使用的材料


641
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:24,466
这次不是过度开发的红石装置

642
00:14:24,466 --> 00:14:26,833
我们将使用更糟糕的方法

643
00:14:26,833 --> 00:14:29,666

我们使用SFM暴力完成任务


644
00:14:29,833 --> 00:14:32,866
既然我们在Stack Overflow上找不到解决方案

645
00:14:32,866 --> 00:14:34,766
我们害怕for循环

646
00:14:34,766 --> 00:14:36,566
我们将做一长串的else if

647
00:14:36,566 --> 00:14:38,700
就像程序员幽默meme一样

648
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:41,233
拜托，能跑就行

649
00:14:41,466 --> 00:14:43,100
不管怎样

650
00:14:43,100 --> 00:14:46,566
我们现在着手制作星门

651
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:48,266
那东西有很多步骤

652
00:14:48,266 --> 00:14:50,200
并需要数万亿件物品

653
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:53,800
所以我们将任务抽丝剥茧

654
00:14:54,066 --> 00:14:57,333
当AE自动完成任务的时候

655
00:14:57,333 --> 00:15:00,900
我们可以致力于改善基础设施

656
00:15:01,366 --> 00:15:04,566
我们首先要解决的是电力生产

657
00:15:04,766 --> 00:15:08,300
当然，这需要很多宇宙素

658
00:15:08,300 --> 00:15:11,800
我们可以用一些星阵加速它

659
00:15:12,266 --> 00:15:14,300
然后我们制造成千上万的机器

660
00:15:14,300 --> 00:15:16,466
加快一切的制作

661
00:15:16,900 --> 00:15:17,366
最后

662
00:15:17,366 --> 00:15:21,700
我们尽可能多地超频慢速的东西

663
00:15:21,700 --> 00:15:26,766
将最慢零件的制作时间缩短1000倍

664
00:15:27,066 --> 00:15:29,566
现在我们已经达到了TPS上限

665
00:15:29,566 --> 00:15:33,200
所以我们就坐在那里看着星门被制作出来

666
00:15:33,266 --> 00:15:34,900
这花了很多时间

667
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:37,066
但我们设法慢慢建造了它

668
00:15:37,100 --> 00:15:39,633
这是我们最新的造物

669
00:15:39,700 --> 00:15:40,266
然而

670
00:15:40,266 --> 00:15:43,100
当我们完成整合包的最后一个任务时

671
00:15:43,100 --> 00:15:44,900
我们还没有完全完成

672
00:15:44,966 --> 00:15:45,466
确实

673
00:15:45,466 --> 00:15:48,833
如果没有第二套门，这个设备就没用了

674
00:15:48,866 --> 00:15:50,766
所以我们再挂机一会儿

675
00:15:50,766 --> 00:15:53,400
等待AE为我们再造一个

676
00:15:53,500 --> 00:15:55,766
在某个隐蔽的地方建造后

677
00:15:55,766 --> 00:15:59,700
我们在主星门通过拨号它的地址来连接它

678
00:15:59,700 --> 00:16:02,866
我们确认了一下，然后盯着动画

679
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:13,666
现在是时候展示这个入口带我们去的神秘地方了

680
00:16:13,900 --> 00:16:15,033
如你所见

681
00:16:15,033 --> 00:16:19,566
这个地方到处都是奇怪的绿色东西

682
00:16:19,633 --> 00:16:21,766
但我觉得我们今天做得够多了

683
00:16:21,766 --> 00:16:25,766
我们可以考虑下一季再碰这些东西

684
00:16:25,866 --> 00:16:27,066
和往常一样

685
00:16:27,066 --> 00:16:28,700
问候前

686
00:16:28,700 --> 00:16:32,200
我们将反思今天学到的东西

687
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:36,433
经过我们所有的汗水和泪水才走到这一步

688
00:16:36,433 --> 00:16:40,000
真正的奖励不是任务完成后的奖励

689
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:43,100
而是我们一路上做出的石头粉

690
00:16:43,100 --> 00:16:44,000
拜拜

